# Drop the useless index column if it exists
for name in ["headers", "img_info", "popularity", "users"]:
    df_obj = globals()[name]
    if "Unnamed: 0" in df_obj.columns:
        globals()[name] = df_obj.drop(columns=["Unnamed: 0"])

# Inspect columns in each table

In[8]:
# Find all columns that start with "Day"
day_cols = [c for c in popularity.columns if c.startswith("Day")]

# Compute total views across all days
popularity["popularity_score"] = popularity[day_cols].sum(axis=1)

# Define top 25% as popular
q75 = popularity["popularity_score"].quantile(0.75)
popularity["is_popular"] = (popularity["popularity_score"] >= q75).astype(int)

popularity[["FlickrId", "popularity_score", "is_popular"]].head()

In[11]:
rows = []

for i, img_path in enumerate(image_paths[:3000]):  # start with 3000 so it runs faster
    if i % 200 == 0:
        print(f"Processing {i}/{len(image_paths)}")

    results = model(img_path)[0]
    boxes = results.boxes

    row = {"image_file": img_path.name}

    if boxes is not None and len(boxes) > 0:
        class_ids = boxes.cls.cpu().numpy().astype(int)
        unique_ids, counts = np.unique(class_ids, return_counts=True)

        for cid, cnt in zip(unique_ids, counts):
            class_name = results.names[int(cid)]
            row[f"count_{class_name}"] = cnt

    rows.append(row)

yolo_features = pd.DataFrame(rows).fillna(0)
yolo_features.head()

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report

feature_cols = [c for c in full.columns if c.startswith("count_")]

X = full[feature_cols].fillna(0)
y = full["is_popular"]

# Optionally drop rows where y is NaN (shouldn't happen, but just in case)
mask = y.notna()
X = X[mask]
y = y[mask]

print("Class counts:\n", y.value_counts())

X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=0   #  removed stratify=y
)

model = RandomForestClassifier(
    n_estimators=200,
    max_depth=10,
    random_state=0
)
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

print(classification_report(y_test, model.predict(X_test)))
